And forgive us our trespasses, as we forgive them that tres- pass against us.

What does that mean?

Answer. We ask in this prayer that our Father in heaven may not regard our sin, and may not because of it reject our prayer, for we are not worthy of anything we ask, neither have we deserved it, but that He will grant all to us of His grace, for we sin greatly each day and deserve nothing but punish- ment. And in our turn we will heartily forgive and do good to all those who sin against us.
